s=title> The high seas...</span><hr size=1> Hehehee<br>
<br>
The day grew old, and the beard of our drunken dwarven cleric too...<br>
He aint getting no experience here at his level 49, and the boring &quot;Areeew&quot; cries of them Spectres making no thrill anymore, he decided to lay and sleep some more, leaving the two of us alone...<br>
<br>
Well, good as it went before, last half hour and so we needed no heal, did we grow unwary and felt all to mighty ... indeed we did (: . The setting sun shone its last rays upon a gnomish pair: Mewife Enchantress full of magic might, and a humble yours dearly, clad in black and red armor.<br>
<br>
The Spectre Isle stood agloom mid of Ocean of Tears, and the next boring Spectre emerged out of its forsaken evil plane. The routine movements mewife and me did like so many before: mighty enchatress feared the archevil undead, and it ran. My task to jump it and engulf in slowing darkness seemed no treat like hundreds times before, the striking of my trusty blades quickened to the unseeable blurr under her Celerity spell...<br>
<br>
But lo and behold... was it a nappin world at the dusk (/ooc server lag?) or the jumpy undead that there strutt? (/ooc pathing bug?) could i not hit a good stab on that malicious being. It jumped over the rocks and see, always sorta afront of me. Neither did we wait enough so it attacked the enchantress, so our conjured pair of floating blades that made her pet would lend its help to the nightmare's demise...<br>
<br>
There jumped spectre over rocks, and i levitate-jumped after it, ever at the knifes distance, but never nearer to hit... When we, as a merry go round train hit the ugly spectres brethren that just came to visit us too. Clang clang, a maelstrom of blades and foating green skulls, yours dearly stood with half his life. Running back left-right, the wrong spectre got feared while the other whacked at me unhindered.<br>
<br>
Hmmm.. under those two bubbles, still under wolf spirit form, I called it the day. So we ran for dear life...<br>
<br>
The seas are wide, the seas are bright, where does a rogue hide in all of the Ocean of Tears?<br>
<br>
Holding to someone's motto that I do run faster scared then they do run mad after me, I levitated over sea surface, while the Spectres swam slower below, ever intent on beheading me. Oracle Island came, and the Erollisi sister one, when a BOAT appeared at the dock out of the foggy rain. <br>
<br>
Alas, it moved already, so I set for a desperate course of reaching it floating in mid-sea to the left. At least, I though, have I tried it, counting to reach the solid ground with the rest of my breath when the spectres catch to me. Reaching the boat-side, I sorta floated right into its inner bar cabin!<br>
<br>
Boy, did I relax. I hid too, but knew for sure no monster can attack you on ship, the journey turned into a tourist trip of sorts. I spoke with mewife as she reached the Sister isle too, then sat to learn the gating spell, run on journeman boots some further, then gated afront of hatred-deranged spectre pair!<br>
<br>
Smoking my pipe, as a younger adventurer inspected my gear and commented in awe that his father used to adventure with me in the old dungeon of Paw, did it amuse me to hear the cries from afar:<br>
<br>
/ooc so what moron trained the Spectres to the sister island there?<br>
<br>
as the boat zoned away... <p><BR> </FONT><P><font size=3 color="#000066"><u>Karlek Bubica, 44th season...            </u></font> <BR> <font size=2 color="#660000">  Welfare Consultancy</font>  <BR> <font size=2 color="#996633"><strong>Gnome Rogue on Tunare</strong></FONT><P><P><i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub2.ezboard.com/uvilkatatasavalt.showPublicProfile>Vilkata Tasavalt</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global Rogue</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/20/00 1:38:44 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The high seas...</span><hr size=1> Nice, but I see only one problem.<br>
<br>
Things CAN attack you on the boat.<br>
I was heading over to Butcherblock, with a brief stop-over at those docks in between.  I'm standing there, and all of a sudden, the woman on the docks screamed something about Dark Elves and jumped on the boat!<br>
<br>
She started kicking the crap out of me because I couldn't hit her back, as she kept sliding backwards on the boat...SHE could still hit ME, mind you.<br>
<br>
I finally took her down when I was at 1 bubble of health.  Couldnt loot her cuz her body &quot;floated&quot; away.<br>
<br>
Stupid bugs.<br>
<br>
Vilk<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub2.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kilfara>Kilfara</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Local Rogue</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/20/00 10:49:49 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The high seas...</span><hr size=1> It was probably my second day playing Everquest, when I decided to explore Norrath a little bit and take the boat from Freeport to Faydwer.  The boat pulls up to the dock at the Isle.  I jump off the boat, followed by several other travelers, and the Sea Cyclops!  The monster belts me in the back of the head and I fall to the ground.  It proceeds to kill everyone else from the boat before returning to me, allowing me to see it's massive form before dying.  Frightening for a newbie, but oh soo exciting!  Though we weren't ON the boat, I've heard many stories of the Cyclops attacking people on the boat while it's in transit.<br>
<br>
Kilfara<br>
16th Shadow<br>
Solusek Ro <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub2.ezboard.com/ugrimjawbadflagon.showPublicProfile>Grimjaw Badflagon</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global Rogue</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/21/00 7:17:49 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The high seas...</span><hr size=1> Yeah was on the boat when the cyclops wiped out nine people on the boat.  Miraculously it didnt get me.  My hide wasnt working right (never does on a boat)but managed to avoid its wrath.<br>
<br>
Stay Frosty <p>Grimjaw Badflagon “Cosmopolitain” Barbarian
